class Solution:
    def canTraverseAllPairs(self, nums: List[int]) -> bool:
        parent = list(range(len(nums)))

        def find(x):
            if parent[x] != x: 
                parent[x] = find(parent[x])
            return parent[x]

        def union(x, y):
            px, py = find(x), find(y)
            if px != py:
                parent[px] = py

        for i in range(len(nums)):
            for j in range(i+1, len(nums)):
                if math.gcd(nums[i], nums[j]) > 1:
                    union(i, j)

        return len({find(i) for i in range(len(nums))}) == 1
```

This implements union-find to check connectivity between all pairs. Time complexity is O(N^2) to perform unions and O(N) to find parents. Overall time complexity is O(N^2). Space complexity is O(N) for the parent array.

